    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<K,​V>, BoundedMap<K,​V>
    public final class LRUCache<K,​V>
extends LinkedHashMap<K,​V>
implements BoundedMap<K,​V>
    A special LinkedHashMap which has a maximum size and whose iteration order is the order in which its entries were last accessed, from least-recently to most-recently.

    This map can be treated as a simple LRU cache. Invoking the Map.put(Object, Object), Map.putIfAbsent(Object, Object), Map.get(Object), Map.getOrDefault(Object, Object), Map.compute(Object, BiFunction), Map.computeIfAbsent(Object, Function), Map.computeIfPresent(Object, BiFunction), or Map.merge(Object, Object, BiFunction) methods results in an access to the corresponding entry (assuming it exists after the invocation completes). The Map.replace(Object, Object) and Map.replace(Object, Object, Object) methods only result in an access of the entry if the value is replaced. The Map.putAll(Map) method generates one entry access for each mapping in the specified map, in the order that key-value mappings are provided by the specified map's entry set iterator. No other methods generate entry accesses. In particular, operations on collection-views do not affect the order of iteration of the backing map.

    Note: This class is provided as a convenience to developers who are making casual use of caching idioms. Production projects should consider using Guava's Caching facility.

    Author:
    Zhenya Leonov
